# Forking a foreign Repository

* Github: Go to the foreign repo and click the **Fork** button (up right)
* Github will fork the repository and present the page of my repo
* Github: Get https address from own repository: Click on **Clone or download** button, choose https and copy address to clipboard.
* Terminal: cd ~/Projekte
* Terminal: Clone repo  **git clone [addres-of-my-repo]**
* Terminal: Go to the new directory: **cd [repo-directory]**
